{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "CriticalSingleScatteringAlbedo",
        "description": "Critical single-scattering albedo at which an aerosol layer transitions from cooling to heating — Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 24 §24.2, Eq. 24.15.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "radiative_forcing"
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "CriticalSingleScatteringAlbedo": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, Chapter 24, Section 24.2, Equation 24.15.",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/aerosol_radiative_forcing.jl:106\nCritical single-scattering albedo from the Charlson et al. two-stream forcing balance, ω_crit = 2·R_s / (2·R_s + β·(1−R_s)²). When ω > ω_crit the aerosol layer cools (scattering dominates); when ω < ω_crit it heats (absorption dominates). Authored as a closed-form algebraic .esm so that, after MTK structural_simplify, the compiled system has zero ODE states and the inline-test runner exercises ω_crit at its observed algebraic value.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-8 / abs=1e-12): the closed-form expression is a small rational function of two dimensionless parameters, so 1e-8 captures float64 roundoff in the multi-step evaluation. abs=1e-12 floors the dark-surface limit (R_s=0.01) where ω_crit ≈ 0.066."
            },
            "variables": {
                "R_s": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.15,
                    "description": "Surface albedo (dimensionless)"
                },
                "β": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.29,
                    "description": "Upscatter fraction (dimensionless)"
                },
                "ω_crit": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Critical single-scattering albedo: ω_crit = 2·R_s / (2·R_s + β·(1−R_s)²).",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    2,
                                    "R_s"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            2,
                                            "R_s"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            "β",
                                            {
                                                "op": "^",
                                                "args": [
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "+",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            1,
                                                            {
                                                                "op": "*",
                                                                "args": [
                                                                    -1,
                                                                    "R_s"
                                                                ]
                                                            }
                                                        ]
                                                    },
                                                    2
                                                ]
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-8,
                "abs": 1e-12
            },
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "table_24_2_default_Rs015_beta029",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream Aerosol.jl `CriticalSingleScatteringAlbedo - Figure 24.2 Validation` testitem default case. Table 24.2 land-surface values R_s=0.15, β=0.29 give ω_crit ≈ 0.589 (upstream asserts ≈ 0.586 with rtol=0.01; we pin the exact analytic value).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.15,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.5887836710661891
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 0.5887836710661891
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_dark_surface_limit",
                    "description": "Dark-surface limit R_s → 0 implies ω_crit → 0. Upstream asserts `ω_crit(R_s=0.01, β=0.29) < 0.1`; we pin the exact analytic value.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.01,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.06573995247001437
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_bright_surface_limit",
                    "description": "Bright-surface limit R_s → 1 implies ω_crit → 1. Upstream asserts `ω_crit(R_s=0.99, β=0.29) > 0.99`; we pin the exact analytic value.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.99,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9999853537498693
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_monotonic_Rs_p1",
                    "description": "Monotonic R_s sweep point (upstream uses R_s ∈ {0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9} at β=0.29 and asserts `issorted(ω_crit_vals)`). R_s = 0.1.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.1,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.45987583352494826
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_monotonic_Rs_p3",
                    "description": "Monotonic R_s sweep point. R_s = 0.3.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.3,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.8085163724565423
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_monotonic_Rs_p5",
                    "description": "Monotonic R_s sweep point. R_s = 0.5.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.5,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9324009324009324
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_monotonic_Rs_p7",
                    "description": "Monotonic R_s sweep point. R_s = 0.7.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.7,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9816983381249562
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_monotonic_Rs_p9",
                    "description": "Monotonic R_s sweep point. R_s = 0.9.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.9,
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9983914803927006
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "beta_sensitivity_low",
                    "description": "Sensitivity to upscatter fraction at fixed R_s = 0.5 (upstream asserts `issorted(ω_crit_vs_beta, rev=true)` over β ∈ {0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 0.4}). β = 0.1 — smaller upscatter → higher ω_crit.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.5,
                        "β": 0.1
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9756097560975611
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "beta_sensitivity_high",
                    "description": "Sensitivity to upscatter fraction at fixed R_s = 0.5. β = 0.4 — larger upscatter → lower ω_crit.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "R_s": 0.5,
                        "β": 0.4
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "ω_crit",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9090909090909091
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_omega_crit_vs_Rs",
                    "description": "Reproduces Figure 24.2 from Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) — critical single-scattering albedo as a function of surface albedo at fixed upscatter fraction β = 0.29 (Table 24.2 land value). The curve rises from ~0 at R_s → 0 toward 1 at R_s → 1, crossing the canonical land value (R_s ≈ 0.15) near ω_crit ≈ 0.59.",
                    "parameters": {
                        "β": 0.29
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "R_s",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.01,
                                    "stop": 0.99,
                                    "count": 60,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "omega_crit_vs_Rs",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Critical single-scattering albedo ω_crit as a function of surface albedo R_s at β = 0.29.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_s",
                                "label": "Surface albedo R_s"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ω_crit",
                                "label": "Critical single-scattering albedo ω_crit"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "figure_24_2_curve_family",
                    "description": "Supplements Figure 24.2 with a sweep over β at fixed R_s — the published figure shows curve families for several β values. Larger β (more backscatter) suppresses ω_crit at every R_s, raising the threshold for net cooling.",
                    "parameters": {
                        "R_s": 0.5
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "β",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.05,
                                    "stop": 0.5,
                                    "count": 40,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "omega_crit_vs_beta",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Critical single-scattering albedo ω_crit as a function of upscatter fraction β at R_s = 0.5.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "β",
                                "label": "Upscatter fraction β"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "ω_crit",
                                "label": "Critical single-scattering albedo ω_crit"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "Rs_beta_joint_sweep",
                    "description": "Joint sensitivity of ω_crit to surface albedo and upscatter fraction. Heatmap visualizes the Figure 24.2 curve family as ω_crit(R_s, β). Confirms monotonicity: ω_crit increases with R_s and decreases with β.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "R_s",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.01,
                                    "stop": 0.99,
                                    "count": 30,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "β",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.05,
                                    "stop": 0.5,
                                    "count": 20,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "omega_crit_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "ω_crit(R_s, β) heatmap.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "R_s",
                                "label": "Surface albedo R_s"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "β",
                                "label": "Upscatter fraction β"
                            },
                            "value": {
                                "variable": "ω_crit",
                                "reduce": "final"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
